Suspected gunmen on Tuesday abducted a judge at a Sharia Court sitting in Bauren Zakat village in Safana Local Government Area of Katsina State. It was learnt that the attackers broke into the court around 3pm on Tuesday and abducted the judge identified as Alhaji Husaini Sama’ila. Reports indicate that the court was relocated to Safana for sitting due to security reasons and no one could explain why the judge was in the court while strike embarked upon by the Judicial Staff Union of Nigeria (JUSUN) has crippled court activities. It will be recalled that JUSUN commenced industrial action on April 6 to demand compliance with the provisions of Sections 81(3), 121(3) and 162(9) of the 1999 Constitution (as amended) on financial autonomy of the judicial arm at the state level. Katsina is one of the North West states facing serious security challenges. (Daily Sun) ABUJA - The Judiciary Staff Union of Nigeria (JUSUN), has called for the immediate release of Justice Samuel Obayomi of Kogi High Court, who was abducted by unknown gunmen. Mr Kayode Agbarago, National Publicity Secretary, JUSUN, told newsmen on Wednesday in Abuja that the union viewed the abduction of the… In "News" LOKOJA - Judiciary Staff Union of Nigeria (JUSUN), Kogi Chapter, has embarked on a three-day sympathy strike to protest against the abduction of Justice Samuel Obayomi of the State High Court. JUSUN, in a communiqué signed by its Chairman, Daniel Adinoyi at the end of its emergency meeting, condemned the… In "News" By Awayi Kuje Akwanga - The Nasarawa State Chapter of the Judicial Staff Union of Nigeria (JUSUN), on Thursday disrupted court sittings and chased out litigants and lawyers who appeared in courts in Akwanga Local Government Area of the state. NAN reports that the courts that JUSUN shut down the… In "News"